race.comment: Plenty of these close to a win. GOLDEN AGE (8) is long overdue and almost three years since a success, but continues to race well and been oh so close, having placed four of last five. Just missed last time and will give a big sight again. BELLALIQUE (2) has wound up strongly late last couple. Looks well placed here and rates a leading player on best figures.  SOTOMAYOR (7) resumed over 1200m at Colac and found the line strongly for a close-up fifth. Nice return and expected to relish the extra ground. SUZE SPRITZ (10) continues to race well including a last start win at Werribee to win her maiden. Has pace and will give a sight despite the wide draw.
